POLICE SERGEANT GUILTY OF RAPE<
By Damien Brook and Brian Farmer, PA News<
A police sergeant was today convicted of two rapes, an indecent assault and of
burglary with intent to rape.<
Paul Banfield, 33, of St Neots, Cambridgeshire, a custody sergeant at
Cambridge's main police station, was convicted on majority verdicts by a jury at
Nottingham Crown Court.<
He had already admitted three indecent assaults against two different women.<
